This paper deals with the detection of money laundering activities on the Bitcoin network, which involves analyzing transaction graphs and using machine learning classifiers. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with identifying and preventing fraudulent activities. The paper also involves data analysis and machine learning techniques, which could fall under the categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), cybernetics (cs.CY), and databases (cs.DB).
